                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.41/139.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Simpich</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Nogales</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 26, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Arrived from Cananea tonight and at nine p.m. called on Señor Ysidro Fabela,
                    Acting Secretary Foreign Relations for Carranza, and explained to him substance
                    of Department’s telegram regarding case of Benton. Fabela immediately went to
                    Carranza’s room telling me to wait at the Consulate; that he would arrange an
                    interview. I waited two hours. At eleven o’clock Fabela came to Consulate and
                    said that Carranza had agreed to receive me some time to-morrow, February 27;
                    but that Carranza wished to point out that representation regarding the Benton
                    case should not be made through an American Consul but through some diplomatic
                    representative of Great Britain; that Carranza also is dissatisfied that
                    communications concerning the Benton case are being addressed to General Villa
                    instead of to him as he and not Villa is in supreme command of the
                    Constitutionalists. Fabela then left promising to notify me to-morrow at what
                    hour I might see General Carranza.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Simpich</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
